The most effective way for new IT-based companies to target both the Islamic and Chinese markets would be to undertake extensive market research and customize their goods and services to fit the particular demands and preferences of each market. Consideration should be given to cultural sensitivity and language localization. It is essential to comprehend and respect the cultural and religious values of the Muslim market, while ensuring that all materials and communications are translated and presented in a manner that is readily understood by Chinese customers. In addition, establishing partnerships and collaborations with local firms and influencers may be advantageous for engaging and reaching these target consumers. 